per limit of $4.0\\times10^{-5}$ at the 90\\% confidence\nlevel. Taking the total width of the $D_s^{*+}$~(($0.070\\pm0.028$) keV)\npredicted by lattice quantum chromodynamics as input, the decay constant of the\n$D^{*+}_s$ is determined to be $f_{D_s^{*+}}=(213.6{^{+61.0}_{-45.8}}_{\\rm\nstat.}\\pm43.9_{\\rm syst.})$ MeV, corresponding to an upper limit of 353.8 MeV\nat the 90\\% confidence level.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 24 Apr 2023 15:13:52 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-04-25"}
